<br>
I totally agree with this. But the issue of verification came up, and it is valid. I thought that displaying the Ix staff would be good, but S pointed out (basically) that a cleric would have to know ahead of time not to turn it in for the orb. I think something along these lines is good, but how to verify?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> that the list creation was controlled by a few individuals on the server, that the list is controlled by a few individuals on the server, <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
