<br>
As for keeping the list small and randoming... it solves the biggest problems in both FFA and the list.. keeps the list from getting out of control, and keeps the fighting to a minimum.  It requires a little more work than the list for a cleric to join, but less work than FFA for a cleric to reserve and hold  a spawn in FFA.   Even that can easily break down when somebody doesn't want to roll or decides they lost x number of rolls and deserves it more than the other guy.<br>
<br>
It only takes one person/guild to break any system.  A system survives by being as flexible and fair as possible.   Trying to maintain a 40-and-growing list is patently unfair to anyone trying to join in late....only a handfull of the clerics ahead are actually there to make claim.<br>
<br>
Ragefire sucks.... no system is gonna not upset somebody if they *expect* their epic in any kind of timely fasion.   <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
